						<p>From October 25 to October 30, 2020, you will discover what has drawn people to Sicily, known
							as the &ldquo;eternal crossroads of the Mediterranean,&rdquo; for centuries. Lying just a
							few miles across the water from the Italian mainland, the island has a distinct history,
							culture, cuisine and character that can only be described as Sicilian. From towering Mount
							Etna to ancient Greek and Roman ruins to charming seaside villages, Sicily has something to
							capture every imagination. Ricoh has arranged hosted activities and evening events to ensure
							you experience the very best the island has to offer.</p>
						<p>Speaking of the best, you will stay at the award-winning <a
								href="https://www.belmond.com/hotels/europe/italy/taormina/belmond-villa-sant-andrea/">Belmond
